4 A JOINT RESOLUTION OF THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
5 MONTANA REQUESTING AN INTERIM STUDY EXAMINING WATER REUSE; AND REQUIRING THAT THE
6 FINAL RESULTS OF THE STUDY BE REPORTED TO THE 70TH LEGISLATURE.
7
8 WHEREAS, Montana's water resources are of exceptional quality and are a valuable resource to the
9 residents of the state; and
10 WHEREAS, water reuse, also known as water recycling, is a process in which wastewater is purified
11 for a designated beneficial freshwater purpose; and
12 WHEREAS, the potential uses of recycled water include agricultural, industrial, and municipal
13 purposes; and
14 WHEREAS, water reuse is a tool to promote sustainable and resilient water supplies and protect
15 environmentally sensitive resources; and
16 WHEREAS, there may exist technical, regulatory, financial, and educational roadblocks preventing the
17 implementation of water reuse programs in Montana; and
18 WHEREAS, individualizing levels of treatment for specific uses is more cost and energy efficient than a
19 standardized treatment approach; and
20 WHEREAS, opportunities for water reuse may be underexplored in Montana.
21
22 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF
23 THE STATE OF MONTANA:
24 That the Legislative Council be requested to designate an appropriate interim committee or statutory
25 committee, pursuant to section 5-5-217, MCA to:
26 (1) examine existing statutes and administrative rules related to water reuse;
27 (2) analyze existing reuse infrastructure, including the volume, timing, use, and availability of
28 reused water;
